    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1871-11-23T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1871-11-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="110" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d110">
                <head>No. 110.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Fish</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Wing</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                        of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1871-11-23">
                            <hi rend="italic">November</hi> 23,
                                    1871</date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 65.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Your dispatch, No. 151, of the 17th
                            ultimo, in relation to the case of Doctor L. D. Wilson, has been
                            received.</p>
                <p>With reference to his case you state: 1st. That his imprisonment was the
                            result of mistaken identity $ 2d. That it embodies a flagrant case of
                            outrage.</p>
                <p>In reply, I have to request that you will furnish farther explanations to
                            sustain those statements.</p>
                <p>I am, &amp;c,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>HAMILTON FISH.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
